{{Quote|At least I'm still not as bad as ''that'' bloated pus-bag.|[[Eugene Talmont]], paraphrasing Hutt employees|<ref name="Underworld">{{InsiderCite|89|Underworld: A Galaxy of Scum and Villainy}}</ref>}}
'''The Hutt Mirror''' was a phenomenon that occurred when a person in a [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] employment allowed themselves to commit deeply atrocious acts under the rationale that they were still not as bad as their even more depraved employer.<ref name="Underworld" />

